The paper deals with a cyber-physical attack involving additive manufacturing, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and cyber-physical systems (cs.CY). The paper also proposes a systematic approach and methodology, which could fall under software engineering (cs.SE) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the experimental proof involves the use of a quadcopter UAV, which could fall under human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
